The paper introduces a new automata model for processing data words, which is relevant to several areas of computer science. The paper discusses the expressiveness and properties of the new model, which are relevant to the theory of formal languages and automata (cs.FL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), programming languages (cs.PL), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents a learning algorithm for the new model, which is relevant to the area of computational learning theory (cs.LO).
